  'Description': '{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"","text":"Creativity is not a divine gift conceded only to a few.\\u00a0It is a heritage of everyone, but people lose their creative potential through life due to many different reasons.But don\\u2019t worry, it can be turned around! With the combination of knowledge, tools, exercises and tasks,\\u00a0it is possible to bring back to life the creativity inside you!For this reason, this course presents all the stages of the creative process and, for each phase, it teaches a collection of tools and techniques which aim to stimulate and guide creativity! \\u00a0In total,\\u00a0you will learn more than THIRTY tools and techniques which stimulate the creative process!\\u00a0They come from different areas and are not restricted only to the famous Brainstorming and Mind Maps.\\u00a0\\u00a0Of course, such tools are also explained in the course, but you will learn many others to support creativity, which will\\u00a0help you think outside the box and have original ideas!To make your life easier, all these tools are accompanied by\\u00a0support materials that were developed exclusively for this course and that can be downloaded and printed\\u00a0in order to be used where and when you need them!\\u00a0In this course, you will learn:- Ways to identify opportunities and have ideias, through tools such as\\u00a0Convergence Map, Behavioral Tendencies Map, Popular Media Scanning, amongst others;- Forms to cllect data that relate directly or indirectly to your idea, like\\u00a0Eras Map, Types of Innovation Evaluation, Sociocultural Scanning, etc;- Tips to incubate your idea with the development of activities and challenges, based on\\u00a0Creative Idleness;- Many practices to warm up you ideas, such as\\u00a0Tool 635, Scamper, 4 Types of Brainstorming, Mind Map, Wordcloud, amongst others;- Practices to illuminate and evalate your ideas, like\\u00a0Stakeholder Evaluation, 6 Hats, Role Playing Game and Attributes Evaluation, etc.;- Ways to elaborate your idea through\\u00a0Moodboaboards, Canvas, Storyboard, 5W1H,\\u00a0and others;- And, finally, you will get to know tools to\\u00a0evaluate your idea with potential users, partners and in the market.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}',
