  'Description': '{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"","text":"CSS\\u00a0- short for Cascading Style Sheets - is a \\"programming language\\" you use to turn your raw HTML\\u00a0pages into real beautiful websites.This course covers it all - we start at the very basics (What is CSS?\\u00a0How does it work?\\u00a0How do you use it)?\\u00a0and gradually dive in deeper and deeper. And we do this by showing both practical examples as well as the theory behind it.Getting started with CSS\\u00a0might look easy but there actually is a lot of depth to CSS\\u00a0- hence this course provides different \\"Tracks\\"\\u00a0or \\"Entry points\\"\\u00a0to exactly meet your demands and reflect you current knowledge level:The Basics Track:\\u00a0Start from scratch, learn CSS\\u00a0from the ground up. You start with lecture 1 and simply follow through to the end.The Advanced Track:\\u00a0You already know the CSS\\u00a0basics, you know what selectors are and how it works but you want to dive in deeper and learn some advanced features and usages.The Expert Track:\\u00a0You got the advanced knowledge, too, but you want to dive into things like Flexbox, CSS\\u00a0Grid, CSS\\u00a0Variables or Sass. This track is for you.Of course this course offers the theory and practical examples - we\'ll build an entire real course project throughout the course - but there also are multiple assignments,\\u00a0quizzes and challenges\\u00a0for you\\u00a0to practice individual concepts taught throughout the course.Talking about the course project - we\'ll build the frontend (no backend) of a fictional web hosting company. We\'ll have a starting screen which has different sections, we got a responsive design with an animated side-drawer, we got modals and forms\\u00a0and in general we got a lot of CSS\\u00a0animations, font styles and more!Here\'s what\'s inside the course in detail - this is all also applied to the mentioned course project:The basics about selectors, combinators and how you set up styling rules in generalProperties, values and decalarationsHow specifity and inheritance work\\u00a0and why it\'s called \\"Cascading\\" Style SheetsImportant theoretical concepts like the \\"Box Model\\"How the default position of elements can be changedStyling backgrounds (e.g. gradients)\\u00a0and imagesWhich units and dimensions you typically use in CSS\\u00a0(px, rem, %\\u00a0and more)How JavaScript and CSS\\u00a0interactResponsive design\\u00a0and what \\"Mobile First\\"\\u00a0meansStyling forms and form inputsWorking with text, fonts and text stylesFlexbox!\\u00a0How it works and how to use itUsing the CSS\\u00a0Grid and how it differs from FlexboxTransforming and animating HTML\\u00a0elements with the help of CSSWriting future-proof CSS\\u00a0with features like CSS\\u00a0variables or best-practice class namesUsing Sass and what it actually is all aboutIs this course for you?It\'s for you\\u00a0if ...you started with learning web development and you want to build more beautiful websitesyou already know CSS\\u00a0but want to dive deeperyou\'re using CSS in a trial-and-error manner and want to change this (you should!)You might come back later if ...you\'re an absolute CSS\\u00a0pro and you know the CSS\\u00a0working group drafts by heartyou\'re a backend-only developer (Node, PHP, NO\\u00a0HTML or frontend JavaScript)you\'re a total newcomer to web development and you don\'t\\u00a0know the basics about HTMLIf that sounds good to you, we\'d be more than happy to welcome you in this course!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}',
